Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), indicating possible nephropathy and/or tubular dysfunction. HbA1c is low, ruling out chronic hyperglycemia. No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for possible acute or chronic kidney disease.
